Class Pet

java.lang.Object
Pet
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class Pet extends Object implements Serializable
The Pet class represents a pet in the pet adoption system. It stores details about the pet, such as its ID, name, breed, age, gender, and adoption status. This class also provides methods to retrieve and update the pet's information.

Implements Serializable to allow instances of this class to be serialized for storage or transmission.

Key functionalities include:

  • Retrieving pet details such as name, breed, age, gender, and adoption status
  • Updating pet details
  • Determining the species of the pet based on its ID
  • Checking if the pet is available for adoption

    • getSpecies

      public String getSpecies()
      Determines the species of the pet based on the first letter of its ID.

      For example:

      • "D_12345" returns "Dog"
      • "C_12345" returns "Cat"
      • "B_12345" returns "Bird"
      Returns:
      the species of the pet, or "Unknown" if the ID format is not recognized
